<TITLE> Tax-free income ceiling widens to Tk 1.5 lakh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com) - Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam proposed to raise the ceiling of tax-exempt income to Tk 1.5 lakh from Tk 1.2 lakh for fiscal 2007-08. The adviser also proposed a 10 percent tax rebate on the additional tax paid by those individual taxpayers paying taxes at the highest rate of 25 percent and disclosing more than 10 percent higher income in the assessment year. The tax rates will remain unchanged for the companies at the same level of 2006-07. bd
